# Embedded Server 🌐

## 📖 What is an Embedded Server?

An **Embedded Server** is a web server that is packaged inside the Spring Boot application.

Unlike traditional Java web applications, there is **no need to install or configure an external web server** like Tomcat separately.

Spring Boot automatically starts the embedded server when the application runs.

---

# 🎯 Why Embedded Server?

Before Spring Boot:

❌ Install Tomcat

❌ Configure Tomcat

❌ Deploy WAR File

❌ Restart Server Manually

With Spring Boot:

✅ Built-in Server

✅ Run as a Standalone Application

✅ No Manual Deployment

✅ Faster Development

---

# 🌟 Popular Embedded Servers

Spring Boot supports three embedded servers:

| Server   | Description             |
| -------- | ----------------------- |
| Tomcat   | Default Embedded Server |
| Jetty    | Lightweight Server      |
| Undertow | High Performance Server |

---

# 🚀 Embedded Tomcat

Tomcat is the default server in Spring Boot.

When you add:

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
</dependency>
```

Spring Boot automatically includes Embedded Tomcat.

